Proctor &amp; Gamble has pumped Sh50 million into a clean water distribution initiative in 12 counties in partnership with humanitarian aid organisation World Vision.Makueni, Machakos, Kitui, Kajiado, Taita Taveta, Narok, Kisumu, Isiolo, Marsabit, Elgeyo Marakwet, Baringo and Homa Bay counties will benefit from the programme.The investment is part of P&amp;G&rsquo;s Children&rsquo;s Safe Drinking Water campaign which has been running for the past 10 years. The programme will facilitate the distribution of P&amp;G Purifier of Water sachets designed to purify heavily contaminated water in minutes.Managing director Vivek Sunder said UN Habitat/Unep report indicates 50 per cent of hospital beds are occupied by patients with water-borne diseases.